   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, Southgate Cregmile in Murfreesboro, Tenn. to Mother, 1863, May 3</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>1863 May 3 Southgate Cregmile in Murfreesboro, Tenn., to his Mother (Eleanor Griffin). Updates her on the well being of the hometown boys. On constant watch for Conf. Gen. Bragg to show up there at any time. Describes the forfeiture of weapons and surrender of hundreds of Rebel soldiers due to lack of rations, including one whole division. Union Com. Rosencrans (Old Rosey), preparing to move forward, orders the men to exchange their large tents for small, so they can be carried. Urges her to write soon.</abstract>
